ient. When they find the human in the streets, they noticed it wearing a laser ring. Asuka later comes along, making matter worse, as she becomes a target. The three escape to a warehouse storing some weapons. When the cybernetic human finds them again, Kai shoots at it repeatedly, gradually disabling it and soon causing it to self-destruct.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 7\n| Title               = Purple Destiny\n| TranslitTitle       = P\u0101puru Desutin\u012b\n| NativeTitle         = \u30d1\u30fc\u30d7\u30eb\u30c7\u30b9\u30c6\u30a3\u30cb\u30fc\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|5|13}}\n| ShortSummary        = Kai and Yuki are hired at a library to capture a man wearing a purple mask, who is after the first edition of a comic book series. Leonid, an acquaintance of Yuki, later finds the two in the library. When the masked man appears, it is revealed that he has psychic powers and has been identified as a comic book enthusiast. The masked man becomes weak after using up his powers after being chased.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 8\n| Title               = Interlude: The Chronicle of the Rise and Fall of Tokugawa Ramen\n| TranslitTitle       = Interlude R\u0101men Tokugawa Seisui Ki\n| NativeTitle         = Interlude \u30e9\u30fc\u30e1\u30f3\u7be4\u5ddd\u76db\u8870\u8a18\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|5|20}}\n| ShortSummary        = Kai and Yuki discuss about how Asuka is unable to cook and about how Yuki chooses to protect her. When the three decide to go to a ramen shop, Yuki is displeased with its service. After acquiring the necessary ingredients for the perfect recipe, the three open up their own outdoor ramen shop, attracting many customers. Unfortunately, Asuka accidentally destroys it.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 9\n| Title               = The Bewitched Soul\n| TranslitTitle       = Miseraretaru Tamashii\n| NativeTitle         = \u9b45\u305b\u3089\u308c\u305f\u308b\u9b42\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|5|27}}\n| ShortSummary        = Leonid tells Yuki to convince Kai to dress up like a woman again, setting him up on a date with a client named Edgar Hanson. Kai becomes speechless when Edgar unexpectedly proposes to him. It is soon realized that Edgar is wanted for an arrest, explaining that he is an arms broker in order to secure the alliance of the twelve guerrilla corporations of Gald.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 10\n| Title               = Rewritten Memory\n| TranslitTitle       = Riraiteddo Memor\u012b\n| NativeTitle         = \u30ea\u30e9\u30a4\u30c6\u30c3\u30c9\u30e1\u30e2\u30ea\u30fc\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|6|3}}\n| ShortSummary        = Shin-Lu is released from the hospital and taken to the laboratory to have her memory overridden, unbeknownst to Shen-Long. Later on, Shen-Long encounters Maxim Feller, along with Sherry and Kyou, who are now his new teammates. Kyou provokes Shen-Long into a duel, but Maxim intervenes and restricts Shen-Long's powers. Shin-Lu later confronts Shen-Long about how he put Kai's life in danger by the explosion he caused at Gald.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 11\n| Title               = Sweet Melancholy\n| TranslitTitle       = Suw\u012btto na Y\u016butsu\n| NativeTitle         = \u30b9\u30a6\u30a3\u30fc\u30c8\u306a\u6182\u9b31\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|6|10}}\n| ShortSummary        = Kai becomes a bodyguard for Dzhyuma for a few days. Yuki finds out that Dzhyuma is the adopted son of the president of the anti-psychic weaponry production guerrilla corporation. Kai and Yuki prevent a man from stealing Dzhyuma's research equipment, but the two become suspicious of Dzhyuma's intentions. He momentarily shows his jamming device, capable of weakening the psychics through electromagnetic waves.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 12\n| Title               = Blind Spot\n| TranslitTitle       = Buraindo Supotto\n| NativeTitle         = \u30d6\u30e9\u30a4\u30f3\u30c9\u30b9\u30dd\u30c3\u30c8\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|6|17}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dzhyuma is permitted by Yuki to borrow Kai for his research, yet Kai grows to respect him. While Dzhyuma goes on a date with Asuka, Kai and Yuki walk them from a distance. It is not long before Kai and Yuki are forced to use the jamming device against two psychics sent by Dzhyuma's father. Dzhyuma sends his regards to Kai and Yuki, and he leaves Asuka with a gown as a gift of his affection.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 13\n| Title               = Innocent Enthusiasm\n| TranslitTitle       = Muku Naru J\u014dnetsu\n| NativeTitle         = \u7121\u57a2\u306a\u308b\u60c5\u71b1\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|6|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = Yuki goes to an orphanage to donate, but he is too embarrassed for Kai and Asuka to know. Meanwhile, Kai and Asuka go out to search for a lost cat in the streets. The two eventually track down the lost cat in a restricted area, and they then receive a monetary reward from the owner. Maria later contacts Yuki for him to bring her the psychic that he has been sheltering, not knowing she was referring to Asuka instead of Kai.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 14\n| Title               = Solitary Shooting Star\n| TranslitTitle       = Kodoku na Ry\u016bsei\n| NativeTitle         = \u5b64\u72ec\u306a\u6d41\u661f\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|7|1}}\n| ShortSummary        = Shen-Long begins to see changes in his sister's personality over time. Professor Chigaya summons Shin-Lu to participate in a mock battle against Shen-Long in the training chamber. Shin-Lu easily defeats her brother in combat, to which Eiji compares the psychic abilities of Kai to that of Maxim. Shen-Long is taken to the intensive care unit room, but he disappears when Shin-Lu enters the room.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 15\n| Title               = Residents of Paradise\n| TranslitTitle       = Rakuen no J\u016bnin\n| NativeTitle         = \u697d\u5712\u306e\u4f4f\u4eba\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|7|8}}\n| ShortSummary        = Kai begins to lose control of his psychic powers, and he vanishes right before Asuka's eyes. He appears at a cathedral, where he meets a group of psychic children who called him through telepathy. Kai tries to escape, but he is stopped by Cardinal Ghibelline. After evading to the outside, Kai meets Erimiya, who tells him to discover himself. Soon after, Shen-Long attacks Kai for how Shin-Lu has changed after the explosion at Gald.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 16\n| Title               = Similar Vessels\n| TranslitTitle       = Ainitaru Utsuwa\n| NativeTitle         = \u76f8\u4f3c\u305f\u308b\u5668\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|7|15}}\n| ShortSummary        = Ghibelline proves his knowledge about Kai from research, much to the latter's dismay. After Kai seeing a sickly Raphael being tested against anti-psychic weaponry, Ghibelline requests Kai to stay at the cathedral in order to use his psychic powers to find the Sacrament of Calvaria. Kai encounters Maxim, who attacks him mercilessly. At the same time, Hikaru collapses in Eiji's presence, due to the psychic energy felt through Kai.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 17\n| Title               = Escape to the Light\n| TranslitTitle       = Hikari e no Dasshutsu\n| NativeTitle         = \u5149\u3078\u306e\u8131\u51fa\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|7|22}}\n| ShortSummary        = Kai attempts to release the psychic children from the cathedral, but Ghibelline does any means necessary to prevent th