a\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|7|8}}\n| ShortSummary        = Kai begins to lose control of his psychic powers, and he vanishes right before Asuka's eyes. He appears at a cathedral, where he meets a group of psychic children who called him through telepathy. Kai tries to escape, but he is stopped by Cardinal Ghibelline. After evading to the outside, Kai meets Erimiya, who tells him to discover himself. Soon after, Shen-Long attacks Kai for how Shin-Lu has changed after the explosion at Gald.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 16\n| Title               = Similar Vessels\n| TranslitTitle       = Ainitaru Utsuwa\n| NativeTitle         = \u76f8\u4f3c\u305f\u308b\u5668\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|7|15}}\n| ShortSummary        = Ghibelline proves his knowledge about Kai from research, much to the latter's dismay. After Kai seeing a sickly Raphael being tested against anti-psychic weaponry, Ghibelline requests Kai to stay at the cathedral in order to use his psychic powers to find the Sacrament of Calvaria. Kai encounters Maxim, who attacks him mercilessly. At the same time, Hikaru collapses in Eiji's presence, due to the psychic energy felt through Kai.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 17\n| Title               = Escape to the Light\n| TranslitTitle       = Hikari e no Dasshutsu\n| NativeTitle         = \u5149\u3078\u306e\u8131\u51fa\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|7|22}}\n| ShortSummary        = Kai attempts to release the psychic children from the cathedral, but Ghibelline does any means necessary to prevent the matter. When Raphael becomes separated along with Kai from the other children, he uses telepathy to reach out to and reunite with them, as they all make their way to the outside. Kai asks Yuki to take the psychic children to the orphanage for the time being.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 18\n| Title               = Same Bed, Different Dreams\n| TranslitTitle       = D\u014dsh\u014dimu\n| NativeTitle         = \u540c\u5e8a\u7570\u5922\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|7|29}}\n| ShortSummary        = Shin-Lu tries persuade Kai to return to the ASHURUM corporation, even to the point of singing. Kyou shows up and taunts Kai for being weak, and Shin-Lu also tries to prove to him that she has gotten strong through training. Meanwhile, Asuka is visited by Maria, who wants to bring her to see Erimiya. However, Maxim arrives and tries to capture Asuka for his own purposes, to which Maria does anything she can to prevent that from happening.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 19\n| Title               = As You Are Guided\n| TranslitTitle       = Michibikareru Mama ni\n| NativeTitle         = \u5c0e\u304b\u308c\u308b\u307e\u307e\u306b\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|8|5}}\n| ShortSummary        = Shen-Long takes Shin-Lu back to the ASHURUM corporation, later realizing that Eiji was wounded when Hikaru collapsed. Sherry calls Kyou in for a mission, later recognized as to capture Asuka. After Kai says his farewell to Raphael, he recalls about a discussion with Eiji concerning telepathy. Yuki, who resists working with Maria, learns that Asuka is a psychic. Kai finds out that Yuki and Asuka are headed towards the guerrilla home base.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 20\n| Title               = Intent and Fate\n| TranslitTitle       = Ishi to Unmei\n| NativeTitle         = \u610f\u601d\u3068\u904b\u547d\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|8|12}}\n| ShortSummary        = Kai goes back to the cathedral, surprisingly finding Leonid investigating about the home base, and they soon find an underground passageway that might lead there. Hitomi gives an impatient Shen-Long some information about Shin-Lu's behavioral change after her rehabilitation. Yuki, Asuka, and Maria board with Sherry and Kyou on a ship serviced by Rikumi, but the former three are unaware that they are directing the latter two into the home base.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 21\n| Title               = Cruel Flame\n| TranslitTitle       = Reikoku na Hon\u014d\n| NativeTitle         = \u51b7\u9177\u306a\u708e\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|8|19}}\n| ShortSummary        = Yuki prevents Sherry from stealing Erimiya's will, but he is later charged at by Kyou as a distraction. Erimiya defends himself against Maxim's attacks, but it is not long before he is overwhelmed. Kai appears and defeats Kyou, and he then fights Maxim for Erimiya's life. However, Erimiya's dies in Kai's arms when Maria arrives.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 22\n| Title               = Rhapsody\n| TranslitTitle       = Rapusod\u012b\n| NativeTitle         = \u72c2\u60f3\u66f2\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|8|26}}\n| ShortSummary        = Maria comes to the house to battle Kai, assuming that he was one who killed Erimiya. Kai knocks her unconscious after saying he is not at fault. In the next morning, Kai attempts to reason with Maria, but she leaves by pointing out how the guerrilla corporations treat psychics as weapons rather than as people. Eiji travels to Gald to show Erimiya's will to Ghibelline, convincing an alliance with him.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 23\n| Title               = Distant Dawn\n| TranslitTitle       = T\u014di Yoake\n| NativeTitle         = \u9060\u3044\u591c\u660e\u3051\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|9|2}}\n| ShortSummary        = Unable to cease the two military forces of the rivaled corporations from engaging in war, Kai inflames his psychic energy and eradicates the area. This has an effect upon Hikaru, who calls out for Kai, although Asuka is somehow able to hear her voice as well. Sherry and Shin-Lu prepare to head towards the home base. Maxim, now recuperated, fails to tell Eiji that he dreamed of seeing Kai as his reflection.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 24\n| Title               = Waking Nightmare\n| TranslitTitle       = Mezameshi Akumu\n| NativeTitle         = \u76ee\u899a\u3081\u3057\u60aa\u5922\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|9|9}}\n| ShortSummary        = Asakura unveils to Hitomi that Eiji has not only been altering the memories of the psychics, but has also been planning to create a society of psychics. Meanwhile, Eiji reveals to Kai his superior psychic abilities, while noting that Kai currently has no identity. Asakura further mentions that it is possible to restore the memories of the psychics. Kai finds Shen-Long when he breaks into the laboratory, however Chigaya tries to interfere.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 25\n| Title               = Harvest Time\n| TranslitTitle       = Sh\u016bkaku no Toki\n| NativeTitle         = \u53ce\u7a6b\u306e\u3068\u304d\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|9|16}}\n| ShortSummary        = Eiji bring Hikaru to the home base via helicopter. After making it to the arms hangar, Kai and Shen-Long use a military airplane to travel back to Gald. A wounded Leonid appears at the house with footage of the home base. A cybernetic Kyou soon shows up and attacks Maria, yet Yuki chases him away using the jamming device and a bazooka gun. After viewing the footage, Leonid says that Gald has become an execution site.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 26\n| Title               = The Approaching Daybreak\n| TranslitTitle       = Kitaru Beki Reimei\n| NativeTitle         = \u6765\u308b\u3079\u304d\u9ece\u660e\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2003|9|23}}\n| ShortSummary        = Shen-Long is forced to fight Shin-Lu, and Maria later settles a score with Maxim. Kai goes into the chamber where Hikaru is contained. When Kai is unable to stand his ground against Eiji, Yuki arrives and attempts to save Hikaru. Hikaru emits a burst of light awakening the Sacrament of Calvaria, yet Asuka is able to calm her down from afar. Kai and Eiji disappear as they collide in psychic energy, causing destruction within the city. Yuki, Asuka, and Hikaru all wait for Kai to return back to them one day.\n}}\n|}\n\n===Light novels===\nTwo light novels adaptations of the manga, also written by Yuiga, have been published by [[Square Enix]].<ref name=\"Es Releases\" /> The first volume, ''E's The Time to Baptisma'', was published on February 26, 1999. The second volume, ''E's Unknown Kingdom'', followed on January 27, 2000.<ref name=\"Es Releases\" /><ref name=\"ListOfReleases\">{{cite web |url=http://www.square-enix.co.jp/magazine/lineup-book/sakkabetu/ya.html |script-title=ja:\u4f5c\u5bb6\u540d\u5225\u51fa\u7248\u7269\u4e00\u89a7\uff62\u3084\uff63 |publisher=[[Square Enix]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=November 15, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050309062817/http://www.square-enix.co.jp/magazine/lineup-book/sakkabetu/ya.html |archivedate=March 9, 2005 }}</ref>\n\n===Drama CDs===\n[[Square Enix]] released three drama CDs based around the manga. The first, ''E's Volume 1'' was released on September 25, 1999. The second, ''E'S Vol Extra'', followed on March 24, 2000. The final volume, ''E's Volume 2'', which used the same voice actors as the anime adaptation, was released on September 26, 2003 after the television broadcast concluded.<ref name=\"Es Releases\" /><ref name=\"ListOfReleases\" />\n\n===Other media===\n{{nihongo|''E's Zero World Guidance''|E'S \u30ef\u30fc\u30eb\u30c9\u30ac\u30a4\u30c0\u30f3\u30b9 \u96f6|E'S Waarudo Gaidansu Rei}}, published by Square Enix in August 2003, is a guidebook containing additional information about the various fictional aspects of the series, characters, etc.<ref name=\"Es Releases\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/4757510195/ |title=E'S\u96f6 \u30ef\u30fc\u30eb\u30c9\u30ac\u30a4\u30c0\u30f3\u30b9 (\u30b3\u30df\u30c3\u30af) |publisher=[[Amazon.com|Amazon.co.jp]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=November 15, 2008 }}</ref>\n\n''eSpecial: E's Postcard Book'' contains fifteen postcards featuring characters from the series was published in March 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/4757509138/ |title=eSpecial: E's Postcard Book |publisher=[[Amazon.com|Amazon.co.jp]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=November 15, 2008 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.square-enix.co.jp/magazine/gfantasy/story/es/ Official GFantasy ''E's'' website] {{in lang|ja}}\n* [http://pierrot.jp/archives/tv_list_2000/tv_062.html Official Studio Pierrot ''E's Otherwise'' anime website] {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{ann|manga|2733}}\n\n{{Gangan Comics manga franchises}}\n{{Pierrot (company)}}\n\n[[Category:1997 manga]]\n[[Category:1999 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2000 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2003 anime television series]]\n[[Category:Action anime and manga]]\n[[Category:ADV Films]]\n[[Category:Fantasy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:Gangan Comics manga]]\n[[Category:Science fiction anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen manga]]\n[[Category:Pierrot (company)]]\n[[Category:TV Tokyo shows]]\n", "name_user": "LittleWink", "label": "safe", "comment": "link perWP:HOWTODAB", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E%27s"}
